  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is correct. It&rsquo;s given that triangle R has an area of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"80\"><mn>80</mn></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. The area of a square is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l squared\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> is the side length of the square. It's given that square S has side lengths of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4\"><mn>4</mn></math> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m\"><mi>cm</mi></math>. It follows that the area, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of square S is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 squared\"><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math>. Therefore, the total area, in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"c m squared\"><msup><mi>cm</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, of triangle R and square S is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"80 plus 16\"><mn>80</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"96\"><mn>96</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>",
